Popular Igbo gospel musician, Chinedu Nwadike is dead. According to reports gathered, the gospel singer died in Abuja on Sunday afternoon after losing the fight to blood cancer. Recall that earlier this month, Nwadike cried for help after he was admitted to the Zenith Medical Centre Abuja due to Chronic Kidney disease. He had recovered from the kidney issue and was expected to be transferred to India by this week for treatment of the blood cancer â€“ Leukemia before he took his last breath this afternoon. The gospel singer was married to Sorochi Dora and they are blessed with three children.